        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 7 at 3:17PM MDT by NWS Pocatello ID</headline>
        <description>At 317 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 17
miles south of Lima, or 29 miles northwest of Dubois, moving east at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern Clark
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
